  "title": "Part-Time Accounts Payable Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>1. Job Summary</strong></p><p>This is a part-time role designed to support the Finance department in\nthe accurate and timely processing of all operational payments\nand recording. This role is critical in ensuring that FAS maintains strong\nfinancial governance, meets its obligations to vendors and stakeholders.  The expected commitment is approximately 24 hours per week.</p><p><strong>2. Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure timely processing of invoices and claims with accurate coding for approval as per FAS’s process</li><li>Ensure payments are prepared with high accuracy and on timely manner</li><li>Achieve agreed KPI associated with invoice processing or any other payables related activities</li><li>Update weekly cost trackers and perform month end activities such as preparation of reports</li><li>Ensure FAS policies and procedures are being adhered to at all times</li><li>Handle queries and provide accurate information to stakeholders</li><li>Identify and develop process improvement plans when required</li><li>Participate and contribute in new processes and developments within the Association</li><li>Perform other ad hoc assignments and tasks as and when requested by management</li></ul><p><strong>3. Requirements</strong></p><p>·      Currently pursing a Diploma or Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accountancy, Business, or a related field</p><p>·      1to 2 years of experience is an advantage, but not required for current students with a strong acadmic record</p><p>·      Experience in P2P process and controls is an advantage</p><p>·      Proficient in Microsoft Excel</p><p>·      Ability to work independently</p><p>·      Detailed-oriented</p>",
